{"title_page": "Stephen Hurd", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=July 2015}}\n{{BLP primary sources|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Stephen Hurd\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| image_size          =\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = Stephen Arthur Hurd\n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1968|1|25|mf=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Washington, D.C.]]\n| origin              = \n| instrument          = [[vocals]], [[singer-songwriter]]\n| genre               = [[Contemporary Christian music|CCM]], [[gospel music|gospel]], [[traditional black gospel]], [[urban contemporary gospel]], [[contemporary worship music|praise & worship]]\n| occupation          = [[Singing|Singer]], [[songwriter]]\n| years_active        = 2000&ndash;present\n| label               = Hurd the Word, [[Integrity Media|Integrity]], [[Epic Records|Epic]], [[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]], [[Columbia Records|Columbia]], HYW\n| associated_acts     = Corporate Worship\n| website             = {{URL|hurdthewordmusic.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Stephen Arthur Hurd''' (born January 25, 1968) is an American [[gospel music]]ian. He started his music career, in 2000, with the release of, ''Minister Stephen A. Hurd & Corporate Worship, Vol. 1'', that was released by Hurd the Word Music. His second album, ''In the Overflow, Vol. 2'', was released by [[Integrity Media|Integrity Music]] in 2001. The third release, ''A Call to Worship'', was released by Integrity Records alongside [[Epic Records]] and [[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]] in 2004. This would be his first album to breakthrough on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' magazine]] [[Top Gospel Albums|Gospel Albums]] chart. He released his fourth album, ''My Destiny'', with Integrity Music alongside [[Columbia Records]] in 2006, and this charted on the aforementioned chart. The fifth album, ''Times of Refreshing'', released in 2008 with Integrity Music, again this charted on the aforementioned chart. His sixth album released in 2012 by HYW Music, ''O That Men Would Worship'', and this charted on the aforementioned chart.\n\n==Early life==\nHurd was born on January 25,<ref name=\"TW Birthdate\">{{cite web|title=No my birthday is Jan 25th same day Deitrick Haddon CD drops |url=https://twitter.com/stephenhurd/status/25202892004659200|first=Stephen|last=Hurd|publisher=[[Twitter]] official account|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> 1968,<ref name=\"GE\">{{cite journal|title=Uncloudy Days: The Gospel Music Encyclopedia|first=Bil|last=Carpenter|year=2005|page=203}}</ref> as Stephen Arthur Hurd,<ref name=\"BMI\">{{cite web|title=Songwriter/Composer: HURD STEPHEN ARTHUR|url=http://repertoire.bmi.com/writer.asp?blnWriter=True&blnPublisher=True&blnArtist=True&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&querytype=WriterID&keyid=546372&keyname=HURD+STEPHEN+ARTHUR&CAE=180067485&Affiliation=BMI|publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.]]|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> in [[Washington, D.C.]],<ref name=\"GE\"/><ref name=\"AM Bio\">{{cite web|title=Stephen A. Hurd : Biography |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/stephen-a-hurd-mn0000749509/biography|first=Steve|last=Leggett|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> where he was reared in the church. After graduating from The [[Duke Ellington School of the Arts]], he attended [[Howard University]].<ref name=\"GE\"/> He became an ordained minister in 1988, at which point he started leading worship services at local churches.<ref name=\"GE\"/>\n\n==Music career==\nHe began Corporate Worship in 1999, and they released a few albums under that moniker.<ref name=\"GE\"/> His solo music career started in 2000, with the release of ''Minister Stephen A. Hurd & Corporate Worship, Vol. 1'' by Hurd the Word Music,<ref name=\"AM Disc\">{{cite web|title=Stephen A. Hurd : Discography |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/stephen-a-hurd-mn0000749509/discography|author=[[AllMusic]]|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> yet this failed to chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\">{{cite web|title=Stephen A. Hurd : Awards|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/stephen-a-hurd-mn0000749509/awards|author=[[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]|website=[[AllMusic]]|access-date=March 28, 2015}}</ref> His subsequent album, ''In the Overflow, Vol. 2'', was released by [[Integrity Media|Integrity Music]] in 2001,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this did not chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> The next album, ''A Call to Worship'', was released by Integrity Music alongside [[Epic Records]] and [[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]] on June 8, 2004,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this was his first release to break through on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' magazine]] [[Top Gospel Albums|Gospel Albums]] chart, at No. 15.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> He released ''My Destiny'', with Integrity Music in association with [[Columbia Records]], on October 3, 2006,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this peaked at No. 11 on the Gospel Albums chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> The following album, ''Times of Refreshing'', was released on October 14, 2008 by Integrity Music,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this charted at No. 8 on the Gospel Albums chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> His latest release, ''O That Men Would Worship'', was released by HYW Music in 2012,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and the album again placed at No. 8 on the aforementioned chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/>\n\n==Discography==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak chart positions<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/>\n|-\n!style=\"width:3em; font-size:90%\"|[[Top Gospel Albums|US<br>Gos]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Minister Stephen A. Hurd & Corporate Worship, Vol. 1''\n|\n* Released: 2000\n* {{nowrap|Label: Hurd the Word}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| \u2013\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''In the Overflow, Vol. 2''\n|\n* Released: 2001\n* {{nowrap|Label: [[Integrity Media|Integrity]]}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| \u2013\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''A Call to Worship''\n|\n* Released: June 8, 2004\n* {{nowrap|Label: Integrity/[[Epic Records|Epic]]/[[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]]}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 15\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''My Destiny''\n|\n* Released: October 3, 2006\n* {{nowrap|Label: Integrity/[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 11\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Times of Refreshing''\n|\n* Released: October 14, 2008\n* {{nowrap|Label: Integrity}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 8\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''O That Men Would Worship''\n|\n* Released: 2012\n* {{nowrap|Label: HWM}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 8\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.hurdthewordmusic.com/ Official website]\n* [http://www.crossrhythms.co.uk/artists/Stephen_Hurd/13472/ ''Cross Rhythms'' profile]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hurd, Stephen}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American musicians]]\n[[Category:African-American Christians]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:American male songwriters]]\n[[Category:Epic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=July 2015}}\n{{primary|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Stephen Hurd\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| image_size          =\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = Stephen Arthur Hurd\n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1968|1|25|mf=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Washington, D.C.]]\n| origin              = \n| instrument          = [[vocals]], [[singer-songwriter]]\n| genre               = [[Contemporary Christian music|CCM]], [[gospel music|gospel]], [[traditional black gospel]], [[urban contemporary gospel]], [[contemporary worship music|praise & worship]]\n| occupation          = [[Singing|Singer]], [[songwriter]]\n| years_active        = 2000&ndash;present\n| label               = Hurd the Word, [[Integrity Media|Integrity]], [[Epic Records|Epic]], [[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]], [[Columbia Records|Columbia]], HYW\n| associated_acts     = Corporate Worship\n| website             = {{URL|hurdthewordmusic.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Stephen Arthur Hurd''' (born January 25, 1968) is an American [[gospel music]]ian. He started his music career, in 2000, with the release of, ''Minister Stephen A. Hurd & Corporate Worship, Vol. 1'', that was released by Hurd the Word Music. His second album, ''In the Overflow, Vol. 2'', was released by [[Integrity Media|Integrity Music]] in 2001. The third release, ''A Call to Worship'', was released by Integrity Records alongside [[Epic Records]] and [[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]] in 2004. This would be his first album to breakthrough on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' magazine]] [[Top Gospel Albums|Gospel Albums]] chart. He released his fourth album, ''My Destiny'', with Integrity Music alongside [[Columbia Records]] in 2006, and this charted on the aforementioned chart. The fifth album, ''Times of Refreshing'', released in 2008 with Integrity Music, again this charted on the aforementioned chart. His sixth album released in 2012 by HYW Music, ''O That Men Would Worship'', and this charted on the aforementioned chart.\n\n==Early life==\nHurd was born on January 25,<ref name=\"TW Birthdate\">{{cite web|title=No my birthday is Jan 25th same day Deitrick Haddon CD drops |url=https://twitter.com/stephenhurd/status/25202892004659200|first=Stephen|last=Hurd|publisher=[[Twitter]] official account|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> 1968,<ref name=\"GE\">{{cite journal|title=Uncloudy Days: The Gospel Music Encyclopedia|first=Bil|last=Carpenter|year=2005|page=203}}</ref> as Stephen Arthur Hurd,<ref name=\"BMI\">{{cite web|title=Songwriter/Composer: HURD STEPHEN ARTHUR|url=http://repertoire.bmi.com/writer.asp?blnWriter=True&blnPublisher=True&blnArtist=True&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&querytype=WriterID&keyid=546372&keyname=HURD+STEPHEN+ARTHUR&CAE=180067485&Affiliation=BMI|publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.]]|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> in [[Washington, D.C.]],<ref name=\"GE\"/><ref name=\"AM Bio\">{{cite web|title=Stephen A. Hurd : Biography |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/stephen-a-hurd-mn0000749509/biography|first=Steve|last=Leggett|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> where he was reared in the church. After graduating from The [[Duke Ellington School of the Arts]], he attended [[Howard University]].<ref name=\"GE\"/> He became an ordained minister in 1988, at which point he started leading worship services at local churches.<ref name=\"GE\"/>\n\n==Music career==\nHe began Corporate Worship in 1999, and they released a few albums under that moniker.<ref name=\"GE\"/> His solo music career started in 2000, with the release of ''Minister Stephen A. Hurd & Corporate Worship, Vol. 1'' by Hurd the Word Music,<ref name=\"AM Disc\">{{cite web|title=Stephen A. Hurd : Discography |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/stephen-a-hurd-mn0000749509/discography|author=[[AllMusic]]|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> yet this failed to chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\">{{cite web|title=Stephen A. Hurd : Awards|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/stephen-a-hurd-mn0000749509/awards|author=[[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]|website=[[AllMusic]]|access-date=March 28, 2015}}</ref> His subsequent album, ''In the Overflow, Vol. 2'', was released by [[Integrity Media|Integrity Music]] in 2001,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this did not chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> The next album, ''A Call to Worship'', was released by Integrity Music alongside [[Epic Records]] and [[Sony Urban Music|Sony Urban]] on June 8, 2004,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this was his first release to break through on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' magazine]] [[Top Gospel Albums|Gospel Albums]] chart, at No. 15.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> He released ''My Destiny'', with Integrity Music in association with [[Columbia Records]], on October 3, 2006,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this peaked at No. 11 on the Gospel Albums chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> The following album, ''Times of Refreshing'', was released on October 14, 2008 by Integrity Music,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and this charted at No. 8 on the Gospel Albums chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/> His latest release, ''O That Men Would Worship'', was released by HYW Music in 2012,<ref name=\"AM Disc\"/> and the album again placed at No. 8 on the aforementioned chart.<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/>\n\n==Discography==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak chart positions<ref name=\"AM Awards\"/>\n|-\n!style=\"width:3em; font-size:90%\"|[[Top Gospel Albums|US<br>Gos]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Minister Stephen A. Hurd & Corporate Worship, Vol. 1''\n|\n* Released: 2000\n* {{nowrap|Label: Hurd the Word}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| \u2013\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''In the Overflow, Vol. 2''\n|\n* Released: 2001\n* {{nowrap|Label: [[Integrity Media|Integrity]]}}\n* [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| \u2013\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''A Call to Worship''\n|\n* Released: June 8, 2004